The @Inject annotation needs to remain.
This is what I meant
{code}
--- a/hadoop-yarn-project/hadoop-yarn/hadoop-yarn-applications/hadoop-yarn-services-api/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/yarn/service/webapp/ApiServer.java
+++ b/hadoop-yarn-project/hadoop-yarn/hadoop-yarn-applications/hadoop-yarn-services-api/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/yarn/service/webapp/ApiServer.java
@@ -58,12 +58,12 @@
  */
 @Singleton
 @Path(CONTEXT_ROOT)
-public class ApiServer extends WebServices {
+public class ApiServer {

   @Inject
   public ApiServer(Configuration conf) {
     // don't inject, always take appBaseRoot from RM.
-    super(null);
+    super();
   }
{code}

Minor comment -
{code}
+      if(enableServiceApi) {
{code}
A space should be added between if and (

Thanks Eric, looks like a few things can be removed in the patch:
The constructor:
{code}
public ApiServer() {   
   super(); 
}
{code}
This comment:
// don't inject, always take appBaseRoot from RM.
And the “hadoop-yarn-server-common” dependency added in the pom.xml, since it doesn't inherit WebServices class anymore

